                                         CAPE TOWN â€“ Western Cape authorities are investigating the cause of a crash in Cape Town that left two people dead. The incident took place on the N1 in Belville during the early hours of Sunday morning. It's understood three cars had collided, with one overturning, leaving one male and one female dead. ER24'S Werner Vermaak says authorities who were on the scene are looking into the circumstances which lead to the incident.